1
00:00:00,849 --> 00:00:06,090
Hey guys, in this video I will show you how
I read the price action in order to determine

2
00:00:06,090 --> 00:00:11,360
if the bulls or the bears are in control of
the market and we’ll also try to establish

3
00:00:11,360 --> 00:00:17,450
the momentum of the market by analyzing the
bull and the bear candles during a trend.

4
00:00:17,450 --> 00:00:19,840
So, what is price action?

5
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:26,310
Price action is a representation of a price
movement on a given chart and in its core

6
00:00:26,310 --> 00:00:31,810
it’s basically a representation of the behavior
of the market participants, namely the bulls

7
00:00:31,810 --> 00:00:33,379
and the bears.

8
00:00:33,379 --> 00:00:39,280
The bulls want to move the market up, and
their strength is represented by upward bars

9
00:00:39,280 --> 00:00:46,579
and the bears want to move the market down,
and their strength is represented by downward

10
00:00:46,579 --> 00:00:47,829
bars.

11
00:00:47,829 --> 00:00:54,359
Every bar on a given chart is basically a
battle between bulls and bears.

12
00:00:54,359 --> 00:01:00,260
When we read the price action on a chart,
we don’t have to over analyze and complicate

13
00:01:00,260 --> 00:01:05,420
our trading, we just have to determine whether
the bulls or the bears are in control of the

14
00:01:05,420 --> 00:01:07,390
market.

15
00:01:07,390 --> 00:01:08,430
How we do that?

16
00:01:08,430 --> 00:01:14,590
By analyzing the bull bars- the green ones,
and the bear bars – the red ones.

17
00:01:14,590 --> 00:01:20,570
Before we begin, let me be clear on something,
we will not look at candlestick patterns yet,

18
00:01:20,570 --> 00:01:23,630
we will look at much simpler and clearer clues.

19
00:01:23,630 --> 00:01:29,780
So, a market controlled by bulls is often
characterized by the following bar patterns:

20
00:01:29,780 --> 00:01:36,980
First, then obvious one is that we have more
bull bars than bears bars.

21
00:01:36,980 --> 00:01:45,990
When he see this on our charts, this means
that the bulls have more power and are increasingly

22
00:01:45,990 --> 00:01:57,840
moving the market upwards
Also, we will see consecutive bull bars.

23
00:01:57,840 --> 00:02:06,329
Consecutive bull bars is a clear indication
of a bullish momentum

24
00:02:06,329 --> 00:02:14,890
In a bull market, the green bodies are bigger
than the red bodies.

25
00:02:14,890 --> 00:02:20,540
When he see this on our charts that’s a
signal that the bulls have more strength than

26
00:02:20,540 --> 00:02:23,440
the bears.

27
00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:32,410
Also, during a bull controlled market, we
will see the green bars closing near their

28
00:02:32,410 --> 00:02:33,880
highs.

29
00:02:33,880 --> 00:02:42,940
This suggests a good momentum on the upside,
because the bulls are trying to maintain the

30
00:02:42,940 --> 00:02:47,200
prices higher.

31
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:52,980
We will also see a lot of wicks below the
green bars.

32
00:02:52,980 --> 00:02:59,000
This also represents a good signal that the
bulls are in control of the market and that

33
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:04,760
are trying to push the prices upwards.

34
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:13,950
When we see the green bodies getting bigger
this signals a clear bullish momentum.

35
00:03:13,950 --> 00:03:21,200
This kind of price action suggests that the
bears are unable to compete with the strength

36
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:22,820
of the bulls.

37
00:03:22,820 --> 00:03:33,890
Also, during a market controlled by bulls,
the red bars are getting smaller, as the bears

38
00:03:33,890 --> 00:03:38,140
can’t drive the prices down.

39
00:03:38,140 --> 00:03:44,850
Now, let’s look at the bar patterns for
a market controlled by the bears.

40
00:03:44,850 --> 00:03:51,250
First, we have more bear bars than bull bars.

41
00:03:51,250 --> 00:03:58,870
This means that the bears have more power
and are moving the market downwards.

42
00:03:58,870 --> 00:04:05,620
Also, we will see consecutive bear bars.

43
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:14,480
Consecutive bear bars is an obvious indication
of a bearish momentum.

44
00:04:14,480 --> 00:04:22,370
In a bear market, the red bodies are bigger
than the green bodies.

45
00:04:22,370 --> 00:04:31,710
This kind of price action suggests that that
the bears have more strength than the bulls.

46
00:04:31,710 --> 00:04:42,520
Also, during a bear controlled market, we
will see the closing red bars near their lows.

47
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:52,160
This price action suggests a good momentum
on the downside.

48
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:59,820
We will also see a lot of wicks above the
red bars.

49
00:04:59,820 --> 00:05:06,090
This represents a good signal that the bears
are in control of the market and that are

50
00:05:06,090 --> 00:05:13,940
successfully push the prices downwards, despite
the initial reaction of the bulls.

51
00:05:13,940 --> 00:05:26,070
Also, when we see the red bodies getting bigger
this signals a clear bearish momentum.

52
00:05:26,070 --> 00:05:31,389
This is a good indication that the bulls are
unable to compete with the strength of the

53
00:05:31,389 --> 00:05:33,910
bears.

54
00:05:33,910 --> 00:05:43,770
Also, during a market controlled by bears,
the green bars are getting smaller and smaller.

55
00:05:43,770 --> 00:05:55,139
This price action indicates that the bulls
can’t drive the prices upward.

56
00:05:55,139 --> 00:06:01,870
Now that we know what to look at when we analyze
a chart, let’s take a couple of examples.

57
00:06:01,870 --> 00:06:07,280
Here’s a bull controlled market on the EUR/USD
on the daily chart.

58
00:06:07,280 --> 00:06:13,180
For a better overview, we added a 50-period
exponential moving average to gain a better

59
00:06:13,180 --> 00:06:16,080
perspective on the market.

60
00:06:16,080 --> 00:06:22,520
Once the price action started to move in higher
highs and higher lows, and the price stabilized

61
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:28,880
above the moving average, the bulls took control
of the market.

62
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:39,260
We see consecutive bull bars, big body candles,
green bars closing near their highs, wicks

63
00:06:39,260 --> 00:06:45,560
below the bars, green bars becoming bigger.

64
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:52,370
As long as the price continues to record higher
highs and higher lows this should be considered

65
00:06:52,370 --> 00:07:00,340
a bull controlled market and the only trading
scenario will involve buying positions.

66
00:07:00,340 --> 00:07:05,460
So only long positions during this kind of
price action.

67
00:07:05,460 --> 00:07:08,840
Here’s a similar example on the pound/yen.

68
00:07:08,840 --> 00:07:19,270
The same price action: market starts to record
higher highs and higher lows, price action

69
00:07:19,270 --> 00:07:31,400
above the 50-period moving average, consecutive
bull bars, big body candles, green bars closing

70
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:43,940
near their highs, wicks below the bars, green
bars becoming bigger, red bars getting smaller

71
00:07:43,940 --> 00:07:45,740
and smaller.

72
00:07:45,740 --> 00:07:52,790
Here’s a bear controlled market on the EUR/USD.

73
00:07:52,790 --> 00:07:59,169
First we see the price action making lower
highs and lower lows, as the price closes

74
00:07:59,169 --> 00:08:02,540
below the moving average.

75
00:08:02,540 --> 00:08:05,510
At this moment, the bears took control of
the market.

76
00:08:05,510 --> 00:08:19,479
Observe the consecutive red bars, big red
candles, bear bars closing near their lows,

77
00:08:19,479 --> 00:08:26,910
wicks above the bars, red bars becoming bigger.

78
00:08:26,910 --> 00:08:33,470
As long as the price continues to record lower
highs and lower lows this should be considered

79
00:08:33,470 --> 00:08:41,240
a bear controlled market and the only trading
scenario will involve short positions.

80
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:49,860
In this example, after a strong move downwards,
the bulls gained some strength and push the

81
00:08:49,860 --> 00:08:52,990
market above the moving average.

82
00:08:52,990 --> 00:08:59,269
At this point, this is no longer a bear controlled
market.

83
00:08:59,269 --> 00:09:06,879
I hope you learned a few things from this
that will improve your approach when you trade

84
00:09:06,879 --> 00:09:08,490
the market.

85
00:09:08,490 --> 00:09:15,050
Price action is about simplicity and by analyzing
the market this way, you’ll have more clarity

86
00:09:15,050 --> 00:09:19,379
about the general outlook of the market.

87
00:09:19,379 --> 00:09:24,180
If you got any value from this, please consider
subscribing to our channel and leave us a

88
00:09:24,180 --> 00:09:27,839
like as it would help us a lot in the future.

89
00:09:27,839 --> 00:09:31,919
Until next time.

